The rate of closed string pair production is determined from the
Bogolubov transformations. At high frequencies  this rate
behaves as ()^in _p  ^2 e^/T_H  e^-2 . Recalling the value of the
Hagedorn temperature ,  we see that this
expression diverges exponentially. The closed string pair
production is much more rapid than in the corresponding open
string case, where the exponentials cancelled and the
divergence was at most power law.



